The paper discusses a protocol for verifying public keys without the need for certificate authorities, which is a common topic in the computer security (cs.CR) and cryptography (cs.CY) sub-categories. The use of Tor for key distribution also suggests a potential overlap with the distributed systems (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also touch on information theory (cs.IT) as it discusses the probability of failure in detecting malicious keyservers.
